❗ Problem Being Solved 
Manual data cleaning currently takes 5 hours per week. Human error in Excel formulas often leads to incorrect stock orders, costing the business approximately $200 in monthly waste.
⚡ Automation Potential High (90%) 
The AI handles 100% of the formatting and flagging, leaving only the final confirmation to the manager.
⚠️ Risks and Limitations
•	Risk: AI may misinterpret a valid custom order as a spelling error. (Level: Low)
•	Mitigation: Human-in-the-loop review to make sure they are correct before they are finished


🔄 Version History
•	v1.0 — Initial draft
Prompt: "Clean this cafe sales data and fix the dates."
Output: The AI fixed dates but deleted rows where the product name was misspelled or missing.
Observed effect: Lost 5% of total sales records because the AI "cleaned" by deleting instead of correcting.
Lesson learned: I must add a Negative Constraint to prevent data deletion.
•	v1.2 — Constraint & Role Upgrade 
Change: Assigned "Senior Data Analyst" role and added "Do NOT delete rows; only flag anomalies."
Output: A complete table with corrections clearly labeled in a new column.
Observed effect: 100% data retention. Time spent manually checking errors dropped from 40 mins to 2 mins.
Lesson learned: Explicit instructions on "what not to do" are as important as "what to do."
